Ranger Help for: mix
====================

SYNTAX:      mix salve
             mix poison
             mix poultice
             mix antivenom
             mix stimulant
             mix smoke
             mix weapon paste
USAGE:       Wilderness
SLOT COST:   NA
BASE SP:     20
SKILL TYPE:  survival

SUMMARY:
This skill allows a Ranger to turn wildcraft supplies and saved
profession materials into practical survival consumables.

Poultices heal wounds. Antivenom helps clear poison. Stimulants
restore stamina. Smoke bundles create a brief defensive screen.
Weapon paste sharpens a wielded slash or pierce weapon. Poison still
creates a vial that works with the 'poison arrow' skill.

Poultices, antivenom, stimulants, smoke bundles, and weapon paste scale
with Ranger wilderness skill and level. They are temporary field
preparations and do not save over logout or reboot.

Most recipes use components from forage, mine, quarry, or skin. Some
recipes also consume saved profession herbs or reagents, so Rangers
can live off what they gather instead of returning to town.
